The paper presents an application of Deep Learning techniques, specifically deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN), for detecting extreme weather events in climate datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of CNNs also suggests that the paper may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization of hyper-parameters, which suggests that it may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of Bayesian-based optimization suggests that the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
